A scam is making the rounds involving fake tickets being sold for the Springbok versus All Blacks game on August 6. The Pumas posted on their Facebook page today, February 10, that the test tickets for the game that is to be hosted by the Pumas in Mbombela can only be purchased through Computicket and at Mbombela Stadium. ALSO READ: Taxi operators will not rest until roads improve Any other tickets being sold are fake and will not be valid for entry. “No tickets are yet available, so please wait for the official Pumas announcement on pricing and availability,” said the post.